DETAILS OF OUTSTANDING LIABILITIES

01:01:39.634 --> 01:01:42.970
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

01:01:48.518 --> 01:01:50.937
The government has decided to
inject public funds

01:01:51.020 --> 01:01:53.481
to protect depositors
and stabilize the markets…

01:01:53.564 --> 01:01:55.191
Mom, I'm here.

01:01:55.274 --> 01:01:56.108
What?

01:02:00.112 --> 01:02:01.864
How come you're here
on a weekday afternoon?

01:02:01.948 --> 01:02:04.575
I worked through the night yesterday,

01:02:04.659 --> 01:02:07.370
so they gave me a day off
as a special perk or something.

01:02:09.330 --> 01:02:12.083
Mom, can you pack me some side dishes?

01:02:12.917 --> 01:02:14.585
The family…

01:02:15.294 --> 01:02:17.046
I mean, my colleagues enjoy them so much.

01:02:17.880 --> 01:02:19.715
Of course, I'll pack you some.

01:02:22.593 --> 01:02:23.427
Where's Dad?

01:02:24.136 --> 01:02:25.012
Is he at the market?

01:02:25.596 --> 01:02:27.139
He went to get a refund.

01:02:27.723 --> 01:02:29.350
Business has been slow,

01:02:29.433 --> 01:02:31.644
and your dad did something
out of character.

01:02:31.727 --> 01:02:35.106
Apparently, he bought something
called New Korea.

01:02:35.189 --> 01:02:36.941
It's some kind of investment fund.

01:02:37.024 --> 01:02:37.942
A fund?

01:02:39.277 --> 01:02:40.653
The New Korea Fund?

01:02:40.736 --> 01:02:41.571
Yeah.

01:02:42.071 --> 01:02:44.615
But don't worry,
I told him to sell all of it today.

01:02:49.370 --> 01:02:50.371
Damn it.

01:02:57.753 --> 01:02:59.171
Why do you look like that?

01:02:59.255 --> 01:03:00.506
Did you sell them off?

01:03:03.175 --> 01:03:05.011
It's at minus 80%.

01:03:06.178 --> 01:03:07.513
What?

01:03:07.597 --> 01:03:09.849
Dad, why would you buy that?

01:03:10.349 --> 01:03:13.561
You're the one who told Jang-mi and me
that stocks ruin lives.

01:03:13.644 --> 01:03:14.687
They're not stocks.

01:03:15.271 --> 01:03:17.189
I bought it because it was a fund.

01:03:17.273 --> 01:03:21.527
I asked them for a refund,
and they said it's impossible.

01:03:21.611 --> 01:03:25.072
But Hanmin is
the top-ranked company in the country.

01:03:25.156 --> 01:03:26.365
What are we going to do?

01:03:26.449 --> 01:03:28.117
How could they do this?

01:03:28.200 --> 01:03:30.870
Honey, what are we going to do?

01:03:30.953 --> 01:03:32.955
Damn it…

01:03:47.887 --> 01:03:49.513
It's down 90%!

01:03:49.597 --> 01:03:51.390
You sold me the fund!

01:03:51.474 --> 01:03:54.393
What are you going to do
about my hard-earned money?

01:03:54.477 --> 01:03:55.728
I'm really sorry, ma'am.

01:03:55.811 --> 01:03:58.147
Let me cancel
the automatic transfer first.

01:03:58.230 --> 01:04:01.609
The branch manager said the head office
is working on a resolution.

01:04:02.193 --> 01:04:04.195
Hey, we'll be screwed
if Hanmin goes under!

01:04:04.278 --> 01:04:05.279
You'll pay for this.

01:04:05.363 --> 01:04:06.656
I will sue you!

01:04:08.074 --> 01:04:09.200
Answer me!

01:04:10.451 --> 01:04:12.828
- What are you going to do about this?
- Please don't do this!

01:04:12.912 --> 01:04:14.205
BRANCH MANAGER'S OFFICE

01:04:15.623 --> 01:04:17.208
Sir!

01:04:17.291 --> 01:04:19.502
- Sir!
- Hey!

01:04:19.585 --> 01:04:21.963
- Please help me!
- Give me back my money!

01:04:22.672 --> 01:04:24.465
Please try to calm down.

01:04:25.132 --> 01:04:26.467
What are you going to do?

01:04:26.550 --> 01:04:27.760
I'm so sorry.

01:04:36.352 --> 01:04:38.604
INTERNATIONAL INTEREST RATES, STOCK PRICES

01:04:39.397 --> 01:04:41.649
Doesn't this seem embellished?

01:04:41.732 --> 01:04:43.734
Are these numbers even possible?

01:04:43.818 --> 01:04:45.736
Yeongsan Investment & Securities is out.

01:04:47.488 --> 01:04:48.698
All right, next.

01:04:48.781 --> 01:04:50.783
We're moving on
to Hanmin Investment & Securities.

01:04:50.866 --> 01:04:53.452
- Okay.
- While you review the file,

01:04:53.536 --> 01:04:56.372
you must review
if they'll be able to repay the funds.

01:04:57.164 --> 01:04:58.499
That should be our focus.

01:04:58.582 --> 01:04:59.625
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

01:05:01.627 --> 01:05:02.461
SECURITIES

01:05:02.545 --> 01:05:04.922
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

01:05:05.006 --> 01:05:06.424
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

01:05:06.507 --> 01:05:08.217
Hanmin Investment & Securities

01:05:08.300 --> 01:05:09.427
didn't make the cut?

01:05:09.927 --> 01:05:13.014
Why is our name missing from that roster?

01:05:13.097 --> 01:05:14.223
Why?

01:05:15.099 --> 01:05:17.685
I've never experienced
such humiliation in my life!

01:05:18.519 --> 01:05:19.687
All we did was

01:05:19.770 --> 01:05:22.940
do those other firms a goddamn favor!

01:05:23.024 --> 01:05:24.942
- I'm sorry, sir.
- I'm sorry, sir.

01:05:25.026 --> 01:05:26.527
Unbelievable!

01:05:29.947 --> 01:05:31.407
Goddamn it!

01:05:50.509 --> 01:05:51.343
I'm certain

01:05:52.136 --> 01:05:56.265
I personally handed off
the documents I prepared.

01:06:00.436 --> 01:06:01.395
That day,

01:06:02.229 --> 01:06:04.482
Ms. Hong Jang-mi followed me
to the parking lot.

01:06:04.565 --> 01:06:05.399
You know her, right?

01:06:06.859 --> 01:06:08.152
Ms. Hong did?

01:06:08.235 --> 01:06:09.862
She said I took the wrong envelope,

01:06:09.945 --> 01:06:11.572
and gave me another one.

01:06:12.823 --> 01:06:16.619
Weren't those documents
also prepared by you, Mr. Bang?

01:06:33.511 --> 01:06:35.429
Thank you for your hard work.

01:06:35.513 --> 01:06:37.139
Not at all.

01:06:38.974 --> 01:06:39.934
This is…

01:06:49.443 --> 01:06:51.946
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

01:07:02.832 --> 01:07:04.416
DETAILS OF OUTSTANDING LIABILITIES

01:07:09.171 --> 01:07:10.881
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

01:07:22.768 --> 01:07:24.061
{\an8}JULY, 1997
HONG KONG

01:07:24.145 --> 01:07:27.606
{\an8}The financial crisis that began
in Thailand spread to Indonesia.

01:07:28.190 --> 01:07:29.191
Where will it strike next?

01:07:30.776 --> 01:07:31.861
Korea is next.

01:07:31.944 --> 01:07:34.029
So process my resignation immediately.

01:07:34.113 --> 01:07:36.240
You're anticipating
Korea's financial crisis,

01:07:37.116 --> 01:07:39.118
yet you'll become the president of Hanmin?

01:07:40.161 --> 01:07:44.373
Securities firms have the fastest,
most credible intel on Korean companies.

01:07:44.999 --> 01:07:46.959
When the executives start floundering,

01:07:47.042 --> 01:07:48.502
I'll make a clean sweep.

01:07:51.755 --> 01:07:54.425
Everyone has such aspirations at times.

01:07:55.009 --> 01:07:56.260
Mine's not an aspiration.

01:07:56.760 --> 01:07:59.054
I'm solving a problem
I already know the answer to.

01:08:23.746 --> 01:08:24.788
PUBLIC FUND INJECTION
INTO FINANCIAL SECTOR

01:08:24.872 --> 01:08:25.748
HANMIN EXCLUDED

01:08:39.678 --> 01:08:40.554
That was your doing.

01:08:42.056 --> 01:08:42.973
If we go bankrupt,

01:08:43.057 --> 01:08:44.850
thousands of employees
will be out on the streets.

01:08:44.934 --> 01:08:46.227
Is that the justice you seek?

01:08:46.810 --> 01:08:49.647
Then should I have just let you
cook books and loot public funds?

01:08:51.190 --> 01:08:54.193
Chairman Kang exploits crises
to line his own pockets.

01:08:55.110 --> 01:08:56.904
Would you stay complicit
while his employees, investors,

01:08:56.987 --> 01:08:58.906
and the public
pay the price for his corruption?

01:08:58.989 --> 01:09:00.449
I just did what I had to do.

01:09:00.532 --> 01:09:02.534
I was trying to save my colleagues,

01:09:02.618 --> 01:09:05.162
not to blow the company to pieces!

01:09:05.246 --> 01:09:07.414
Are you using your colleagues
to justify yourself?

01:09:08.374 --> 01:09:10.709
Right. I almost forgot.

01:09:10.793 --> 01:09:14.171
You're so devoted that you even led
the accounting fraud nine years ago.

01:09:17.633 --> 01:09:19.009
We've met before.

01:09:24.390 --> 01:09:25.391
Please take good care of us.

01:09:26.141 --> 01:09:26.976
Thank you.

01:09:27.476 --> 01:09:28.852
Sorry, Keum-bo.

01:09:28.936 --> 01:09:30.813
I'll persuade him to do the right thing.

01:09:32.398 --> 01:09:34.984
…committed suicide by jumping
from his apartment building

01:09:35.067 --> 01:09:36.151
around 3 p.m. today.

01:09:38.487 --> 01:09:41.156
The Hanmin accounting fraud case in 1988.

01:09:42.616 --> 01:09:44.827
Do you remember the accountant
who jumped to his death back then?

01:09:46.954 --> 01:09:48.455
He was my mentor.

01:09:49.373 --> 01:09:50.541
He was my colleague.

01:10:02.261 --> 01:10:03.762
I guess that settles it.

01:10:05.639 --> 01:10:07.349
Even in the thick of the storm…

01:10:10.269 --> 01:10:11.937
we'll never be in the same boat.

01:10:12.855 --> 01:10:13.856
Never.

01:11:00.611 --> 01:11:02.446
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:11:02.529 --> 01:11:04.907
{\an8}All signs point to us
ending the operation.

01:11:05.491 --> 01:11:06.450
{\an8}Let's wrap it up.

01:11:07.409 --> 01:11:08.535
{\an8}But I wasn't trying to hide it.

01:11:08.619 --> 01:11:10.621
{\an8}You never asked who my dad was.

01:11:10.704 --> 01:11:13.832
{\an8}If you think about it,
you're the biggest liar here.

01:11:14.583 --> 01:11:15.417
{\an8}Damn it!

01:11:15.918 --> 01:11:17.544
{\an8}You damn brat!

01:11:19.505 --> 01:11:21.256
{\an8}I'm D.K. Lee of DK Ventures.

01:11:21.340 --> 01:11:23.467
{\an8}If Hanmin goes bankrupt on its own?
That's a win for me.

01:11:24.968 --> 01:11:26.095
{\an8}A 40% staff reduction?

01:11:26.178 --> 01:11:27.471
{\an8}Show respect to your senior.

01:11:27.554 --> 01:11:28.514
{\an8}Senior?

01:11:29.807 --> 01:11:30.974
{\an8}Director Yun, I found it.

01:11:31.058 --> 01:11:32.393
{\an8}The slush fund ledger.

01:11:34.061 --> 01:11:39.066
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim